The **Indole Test** is a biochemical test used to determine the ability of bacteria to ++produce indole from the amino acid tryptophan++. This reaction is mediated by the enzyme `tryptophanase`. The test is one of the four IMViC tests (Indole, Methyl Red, Voges–Proskauer, Citrate) widely used for the identification and differentiation of `Enterobacteriaceae`.
